com.cyc.baseclient.subl.subtypes

Class BasicSublFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.baseclient.cycobject.DefaultCycObject
      • com.cyc.baseclient.subl.subtypes.BasicSublFunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CycObject, SublFunction, Comparable<Object>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractSublMultiArgFunction, AbstractSublNoArgFunction, AbstractSublSingleArgFunction

    public class BasicSublFunction
extends DefaultCycObject
implements SublFunction
    Provides a basic, common implementation of SubLFunction. As with SubLFunction, BasicSubLFunction does not provide a method for evaluating the SubL function, but there are classes which inherit from this one to provide such methods.

    Note that this class also provides all of the methods necessary to satisfy the SublSourceFile interface. A class which extends this class and implements SubLSourceFile can have its sources located and loaded by com.cyc.baseclient.subl.SubLResourceLoader with no additional work, provided that the source file adheres to the conventions described in getSourceFilePath().

      • getSourceFilePath

        public String getSourceFilePath()
        Provides an implementation of SubLSourceFile#getSourceFilePath() . Returns the path of the source file.

        Source file conventions: The filename is assumed to be the function's toString() value, lower-cased, with a ".lisp" suffix. The file is assumed to be located within a directory named "subl" in the root of the classpath. E.g., for a function with the symbol CATEGORIZE-TERM-WRT-API, the file would be expected at subl/categorize-term-wrt-api.lisp.

        Note that this method will only provide a non-null result if the inheriting class implements SublSourceFile.

        Returns:
        the path of the source file.
